# Phase 37 — procedural audio: regenerated on Editor at every Build Everything
# run (deterministic seed). Per D-053 in Docs/Phase35_Continuation_Audit.md,
# the .wav files live under Assets/_Project/Audio/Generated/ and are not
# committed; the C# generator (Phase37_ProceduralAudioStudio.cs) + the Python
# preview script (Tools/audio_generation/generate_audio.py) are the source of
# truth. A future human-authored composer drop into Assets/_Project/Audio/Music/
# (or /Voice/) is committed normally and overrides the procedural baseline.
Assets/_Project/Audio/Generated/
Assets/_Project/Audio/Generated.meta

# Phase 32 — Voice Acting MVP (D-058 + D-059)
# The Piper TTS pipeline (Tools/generate_voices.sh) produces .wav voice
# clips locally on every developer machine. The .wav files are user-
# generated artifacts — not committed. Source of truth is the C# code +
# the line table in Tools/generate_voices.sh + the casting table in
# Docs/VOICE_CASTING.md. A future human-authored or paid-TTS drop into
# Assets/_Project/Audio/Voice/<Character>/ is committed normally and
# overrides the procedural baseline (the runtime can't tell the difference).
Assets/_Project/Audio/Voice/*/*.wav
Assets/_Project/Audio/Voice/*/*.wav.meta

# Piper voice models live under Tools/voice_models/. The .onnx weights +
# .onnx.json configs are 50–70 MB each and trivially re-downloadable from
# https://huggingface.co/rhasspy/piper-voices. The download script
# (Tools/download_voice_models.sh) is the source of truth; the models are
# user-generated artifacts. .gitkeep is committed so the folder exists.
Tools/voice_models/*.onnx
Tools/voice_models/*.onnx.json
